These are the guidelines that shape how you should design the website. You should always follow them.


- Keep the site static -- never rely on a backend server
- For any authentication required -- prompt the user on the frontend to provide API keys instead of assuming they're set in the environenet
- After any large piece of work check that the static site is well formatted and can be served
- Design the site so each project is in a particular link or area from the homepage. Keep the homepage as an index to other parts of the site. 
- Keep all assets in the assets directory with a logical structure that maps to each individual subpage of the homepage or project
